    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Benches designating the location where food and other donations for impoverished or unfortunate people are distributed. Primarily used in historical contexts, for such benches on the premises of churches, hospitals, guilds, private estates, or other establishments that distributed alms.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
